          "order": 1,
          "title": "THE MISSING SEMESTER OF YOUR CS EDUCATION",
          "summary": "Computer Science classes often cover topics such as operating systems and machine learning, but they rarely teach proficiency with tools. This course gives students the opportunity to become proficient in the command line, text editor, version control systems, and more. The mastery of tools not only saves time but also opens up possibilities to solve complex problems. By investing in their tool proficiency, students can make the most of their education and career.",
          "url": "https://missing.csail.mit.edu/?utm_source=tldrnewsletter",
          "reading_time_minutes": null,
          "source_domain": "missing.csail.mit.edu",
          "content_type": "tool",
          "is_sponsor": false
        },
        {
